      "writtenOn": "2019-11-08T15:21:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s interesting that this is a string instead of an enum. I personally prefer Nathan\u0027s approach and use an enum, since it\u0027s more typed. The drawback is to use any new disk type in the future will require a server push but I\u0027m fine with that, as the config values should be validated anyway.\n\nIn the meantime it could be nice to comment since it\u0027s not clear otherwise:\n\n  the current valid values are \"pd-standard\", \"pd-ssd\" and \"local-ssd\".",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 78,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 78,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "d6bd5b566c3addc0c3e83d72aea68c68cbecd44f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
