        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-09T01:33:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Having type and disk_type seems weird, is there anything else we can call this? It doesn\u0027t have to be related to GCE names, it just has to convey to end users. What are the rules for this? Do pd-standard and pd-hdd require PERSISTENT? I think pd is intended to mean \"persistent disk\". If pd requires PERSISTENT and local-ssd requires SCRATCH then we don\u0027t need this.",
      "revId": "d6bd5b566c3addc0c3e83d72aea68c68cbecd44f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
