      "writtenOn": "2019-11-09T01:33:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "From this table it\u0027s sounding like these are the only valid combinations:\npd-standard, PERSISTENT, SCSI, image\npd-ssd, PERSISTENT, SCSI, image\nlocal-ssd, SCRATCH, NVMe, no image\n\nIs anything else valid? If not, then we can use \"type\" to derive everything and don\u0027t need any new fields.\n\nIf you specify local-ssd but omit value for interface does GCE reject the request and require you to specify NVMe explicitly, or does it know to default to NVMe? Same question for SCRATCH.",
      "revId": "d6bd5b566c3addc0c3e83d72aea68c68cbecd44f",
